 animate and support an account of the state as heterogeneous, plural, and erotic. Arguing for the urgent need to put new imaginative forms into practice, Cooper examines how dissident and experimental institutional thinking materialize as people assert a democratic readiness to recraft the state.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aConservatismzUnited States. 0aPolitical participationxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aProgressivism (United States politics) 0aProgressivism (United States politics). 0aRight and left (Political science) 0aRight and left (Political science). 0aSocial actionzUnited States. 0aState, The. 7aLAW / Gender & the Law.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2019z978311069632540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478005575zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478005575423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781478005575.jpg  a978-3-11-069632-5  DUK eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles